laboratory_examinations.findings: Elevated methemoglobin level at 36.9%. After treatment, methemoglobin decreased to 2.0%.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: The methemoglobin level had been elevated at 10% and 20% at 5 and 2 years prior to the latest visit, respectively.

laboratory_examinations.findings: A rare homozygous nonsynonymous variant in exon 3 (NM_000398.7:c.173G>A [p.Arg58Gln], rs121965007) observed. The variant was predicted to be probably damaging by PolyPhen2 and damaging by SIFT.
